# AI Agent Rules

- Each agent lives in `agents/<name>_agent/` with: agent.py, prompt.py, schemas.py, tools.py, state.py, memory.py, tests.py.
- Agents are stateless executors — session state lives in `memory/`.
- Prompts are loaded from `prompts/` templates, never hardcoded in agent.py.
- Tool calls go through `tools/` layer — agents do not call external APIs directly.
- Agent responses must be Pydantic-validated before returning to orchestrator.
- Include confidence score and reasoning summary in agent output schemas.
